Durban - Two men who allegedly broke into a school and stole 14 laptops are expected to appear in Bergville Magistrate's Court on Monday. The suspected aged 18 and 20, were arrested days after they allegedly broke into a school at Upper Tugela in Bergville. They have been charged with housebreaking and theft. According to KZN police spokesperson, Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane, the principal of the school opened a case of burglary following the incident. “Upper Tugela detectives began their investigation and activated their intelligence in the area. "Three days later, the police officers followed up information that led to the recovery of 14 stolen laptops from the school. Two suspects were arrested and charged with burglary.” He added that police were still following up on the four outstanding laptops that were taken from the school. “The arrested suspects will be profiled to establish if they are linked to any other burglary cases reported in the Upper Tugela area.” POST 